My first SCP. Hopefully some of you enjoy it.

Every now and then, I become very aware of the existence of my brain. Just sitting back there. Soft, and fragile, and honestly not so well protected. It scares me a lot. That feeling was the initial inspiration for this story.

Public domain image from Flickr. Slightly edited.

edit: So, funny thing. When I was posting this I briefly considered naming the article  but I thought, nah, too likely that someone used that one already. So then tonight I was browsing the index and noticed that somebody DID use that title before : SCP-150. Not one I'd read. I clicked on it and discovered that 1) it's a parasite, 2) it specifically references Cymothoa exigua, and 3) it includes (among other things) a person's brain being replaced without affecting consciousness. I've gotta say, this freaked me out a bit. I think mine is a fairly different approach to the idea, but wow.





